@startuml component_architecture
title FreeCAD as Main UI — Test Robots in Simulated Environments
caption gz-sim runs headless as a backend; tests live in the repo

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam shadowing false
left to right direction

actor "Human User\n(only sees FreeCAD)" as user
actor "LLM Client\n(Claude Desktop / Code)" as llm

package "FreeCAD GUI Process — the only UI the human sees" #LightBlue {

  component "FreeCAD GUI\n(3D view + Python API)" as fc_gui

  package "Modeling Workbenches" as mod_wbs #White {
    component "Part / Part Design /\nAssembly"  as part_wb
    component "RobotCAD Workbench\n(URDF/SDF export)" as robotcad
  }

  package "Simulation Workbench (Fusion-style)" as sim_wb #LightGoldenRodYellow {
    component "Test Runner\n(load tests/, run all,\npass/fail report)" as test_runner
    component "Sim Controls\n(Play / Pause / Step /\nReset / Reload)" as sim_ctrl
    component "Scenario Picker\n(world + robot + pose)" as scen
    component "Live State Bridge\n(gz-transport subscriber,\n30 Hz Placement updates)" as live_bridge
    component "Camera Viewer\n(Qt panel)"   as cam_panel
    component "Sensor Plots\n(joints, IMU, contacts)" as plots
    component "Run Library\n(past sim_runs)" as runlib
  }

  component "FreeCAD MCP Addon\n(RPC server,\nlocalhost port)" as fc_addon
}

package "FreeCAD MCP Server Process\n(uvx, standalone)" #LightGreen {
  component "FreeCAD MCP Server" as fc_mcp
  component "Git / FS helpers"   as fc_fs
}

package "Gazebo Backend (headless, no GUI)" #LightGray {
  component "Gazebo MCP Server\n(kvgork/gazebo-mcp)" as gz_mcp
  component "ROS 2 + ros_gz bridge"  as ros2
  component "gz-sim -s (server only,\nno Gazebo window)" as gz_sim
}

database "Project Repo (Git)" as repo {
  folder "robots/  *.FCStd"              as fcstd
  folder "worlds/  *.FCStd"              as worldsrc
  folder "generated/  URDF, SDF, meshes" as generated
  folder "tests/  scenarios + assertions" as tests
  folder "sim_runs/  logs, sensor data"  as runs
  file   "project.yaml"                  as manifest
}

' Human path — ONLY through FreeCAD
user --> fc_gui : interact

' LLM path — through MCP servers
user --> llm    : prompts (optional)
llm  --> fc_mcp : MCP
llm  --> gz_mcp : MCP

' Inside FreeCAD: workbenches and animation
sim_wb -[hidden]- mod_wbs
fc_gui <-- live_bridge : updates Placement\n@ 30 Hz
sim_ctrl   --> gz_mcp  : start / pause / step
scen       --> gz_mcp  : load world, spawn
test_runner --> tests  : read scenarios\n+ assertions
test_runner --> gz_mcp : run each scenario
test_runner --> runs   : write pass/fail report
live_bridge<-- gz_sim  : pose / joint state\n(gz transport)
cam_panel  <-- gz_sim  : image stream
plots      <-- gz_sim  : sensor topics
runlib     --> runs    : browse

' MCP server <-> FreeCAD addon
fc_mcp <--> fc_addon : XML-RPC localhost
fc_mcp --> fc_fs     : uses
fc_fs  --> repo      : git, listing,\nscreenshots

' Addon drives FreeCAD + RobotCAD
fc_addon --> fc_gui   : Python API
fc_addon --> robotcad : trigger export
robotcad --> generated: write URDF/SDF/meshes
fc_gui   --> fcstd    : read / write
fc_gui   --> worldsrc : read / write

' Backend internals
gz_mcp <--> ros2
ros2   <--> gz_sim
gz_sim  --> generated : load
gz_sim  --> runs      : record

note right of sim_wb
  This is the Fusion-360 trick:
  switch workbench → switch
  toolbars and panels.
  Same document, same window.
  Modeling ↔ Simulation
  is one click.
end note

note bottom of gz_sim
  Headless: no Gazebo GUI.
  The human never sees a
  Gazebo window — FreeCAD's
  3D view IS the viewer.
end note

@enduml


@startuml sequence_iteration_loop
title Typical iteration loop — "Lengthen the arm 5 cm and test reach"

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor       User
participant "LLM\n(Claude)"   as LLM
participant "FreeCAD MCP"     as FC
participant "FreeCAD GUI"     as GUI
participant "RobotCAD"        as RC
database    "Repo"            as Repo
participant "Gazebo MCP"      as GZ
participant "gz-sim"          as Sim

User -> LLM : "Make the arm 5cm longer\nand check if it reaches the shelf"

== 1. Modify design ==
LLM -> FC  : set_parameter(\n  doc="arm_v3",\n  name="arm_length",\n  value=0.55)
FC  -> GUI : update parametric model
GUI --> FC : ok
FC  --> LLM: updated

== 2. Export URDF ==
LLM -> FC  : export_urdf("arm_v3")
FC  -> RC  : run RobotCAD export
RC  -> Repo: write generated/arm_v3/
RC  --> FC : urdf path
FC  --> LLM: urdf path + commit hash

== 3. Boot Gazebo ==
LLM -> GZ  : load_world("kitchen.sdf")
GZ  -> Sim : launch (headless)
Sim --> GZ : ready
GZ  --> LLM: ok

== 4. Spawn & simulate ==
LLM -> GZ  : spawn_model(urdf, pose)
GZ  -> Sim : spawn entity
Sim --> GZ : entity_id
LLM -> GZ  : step_sim(10s) +\nset target end-effector pose
GZ  -> Sim : run controllers
Sim --> GZ : joint states, sensor frames
GZ  --> LLM: telemetry + camera frame

== 5. Report back ==
LLM -> User : "Yes — it reaches with 3 cm clearance.\nHere's a screenshot."

@enduml


@startuml sequence_human_in_workbench
title Human-driven flow — user clicks Play in the Simulation Workbench

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

actor       User
participant "FreeCAD GUI"           as GUI
participant "Simulation\nWorkbench" as WB
participant "RobotCAD"              as RC
database    "Repo"                  as Repo
participant "gz-sim -s\n(headless)" as Sim

== Switch workspace (Fusion-style) ==
User -> GUI : switch to\nSimulation Workbench
GUI --> User : toolbars + panels swap

== Load scenario ==
User -> WB  : pick world + robot +\ninitial pose, click "Start"
WB   -> RC  : ensure URDF/SDF\nis up to date
RC   -> Repo: write generated/ if stale
WB   -> Sim : start, load world, spawn robot
Sim  --> WB : ready

== Run with live feedback in FreeCAD ==
User -> WB  : click ▶ Play
WB   -> Sim : unpause
loop every tick (~30 Hz)
  Sim --> WB : pose, joint state, sensors
  WB  -> GUI : update Placement on FreeCAD\nobjects (animate the model)
  WB  -> WB  : render camera frame in\nQt panel, append to plots
end

== Pause & inspect ==
User -> WB  : click ⏸ Pause
WB   -> Sim : pause
User -> GUI : orbit / measure /\ntweak parameter
note right of GUI
  Same FreeCAD doc, same 3D view.
  No Gazebo window ever appears.
end note

== Save the run ==
User -> WB  : click "Save run"
WB   -> Sim : stop record
WB   -> Repo: write sim_runs/<timestamp>/
WB   --> User: run saved, listed in Run Library

@enduml



@startuml deployment_docker
title Deployment View — single-host Docker setup

skinparam shadowing false

node "Host machine\n(Linux / WSL2)" as host {

  node "RobotCAD Docker container" as docker {

    node "FreeCAD GUI process\n(the only window the human sees)" as fc_proc {
      component "FreeCAD 1.x"                  as fc
      component "freecad-mcp addon\n(RPC on :5000)" as fcaddon
      component "RobotCAD workbench"           as rcwb
      component "Simulation Workbench\n(controls, viewer,\nlive state bridge)" as cwb
    }

    node "FreeCAD MCP server process\n(uvx freecad-mcp)" as fc_mcp_proc {
      component "MCP server" as fcmcp
    }

    node "Gazebo backend (headless)" as gz_proc {
      component "ROS 2"               as ros
      component "gz-sim -s\n(no GUI)" as gz
      component "gazebo-mcp server"   as gzmcp
    }
  }

  folder "Mounted volume:\n~/projects/myrobot" as vol {
    file "robots/*.FCStd"
    file "worlds/*.FCStd"
    file "generated/"
    file "tests/  (scenarios + assertions)"
    file "sim_runs/  (results, logs)"
  }

  node "Claude Desktop /\nClaude Code" as client
}

client --> fcmcp  : MCP stdio
client --> gzmcp  : MCP stdio
fcmcp  --> fcaddon: XML-RPC\nlocalhost:5000
fcmcp  --> vol    : git, list, screenshots
fcaddon--> rcwb   : trigger export
rcwb   --> vol    : write generated/
gz     --> vol    : load generated/, write sim_runs/
docker --> vol    : bind mount

note right of fc_mcp_proc
  Separate process from FreeCAD.
  Started by the MCP client (uvx)
  on demand. Talks to FreeCAD
  via the addon's RPC port.
end note

note right of docker
  One container keeps versions
  pinned and avoids ROS2 install pain.
  GUI forwarded via X11 / Wayland
  or VNC for the FreeCAD window.
end note

@enduml


@startuml mcp_tool_surface
title MCP tool surface (initial scope)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class "FreeCAD MCP" as F <<server>> {
  + list_projects() : path[]
  + open_document(path)
  + get_object_tree(doc) : tree
  + set_parameter(doc, name, value)
  + compute_inertia(link, density) : tensor
  + add_joint(parent, child, type, axis, limits)
  + export_urdf(robot_name, out_dir) : path
  + export_sdf_world(world_name, out_dir) : path
  + screenshot(view, path)
  + git_commit(message)
}

class "Gazebo MCP" as G <<server>> {
  + load_world(sdf_path)
  + spawn_model(desc, name, pose) : entity_id
  + set_model_state(name, pose, twist)
  + get_model_state(name) : state
  + step_sim(seconds)
  + pause() / resume() / reset()
  + list_sensors(model) : sensor[]
  + get_sensor_data(sensor_name) : data
  + apply_wrench(link, force, torque)
  + record(start|stop, path)
}

class "Repo (Git)" as R <<filesystem>> {
  + robots/*.FCStd
  + worlds/*.FCStd
  + generated/
  + sim_runs/
  + project.yaml
}

F --> R : reads / writes\nFCStd + generated
G --> R : loads from generated\nwrites to sim_runs

note bottom of F
  Start small: list, open,
  set_parameter, export_urdf,
  screenshot. Add the rest
  as scenarios demand.
end note

@enduml


